SHARON E. RUFFING | Round Hill Cemetery

























































Round Hill Cemetery








SHARON E. RUFFING















SHARON E. RUFFING
Born: May 19th, 1962   Died: Apr 6th, 2014

Walk-to-Site Android
Walk-to-Site iPhone
?

Common Issues

Make sure to look at your privacy settings and allow location detection for you device browser.
Iphone Link Not Working? Download Google Maps for iPhone
Try pasting this into your GPS or navigation app: 














Obituary

        Sharon E. Ruffing died Sunday, April 6, 2014 in Jefferson Regional Medical Center.  She was the beloved daughter of Frederick C. and Joyce E. Schmidt of Jefferson Hills and the much loved and cherished wife of Thomas Ruffing of Jefferson Hills.  Her son Thomas C. "T.C." (Leann) Ruffing of Ohio was the love of her life.  The gift of her granddaughter Anna Rose Ruffing made each day special and she thanked God for this very special gift to the family.  Sharon is also survived by her brother Frederick C. (Laurie) Schimdt of West Mifflin and in-laws and other family members.  Sharon was the nurse/office manager for Dr. Ingrid Holman of Elizabeth Township.  She was dedicated to her job and loved her patients.  Sharon's compassion and love extended to all around her including animals, birds, and flowers.  Her life made a difference in this world.  She will forever be remembered by her family and friends.  Friends will be received in the Paul E. Bekavac Funeral Home, Elizabeth on Wednesday, April 9, 2014 from 2 to 4 PM and 6 to 9 PM.  A funeral service will be held on Thursday, April 10, 2014 at 12 Noon in the funeral home chapel with Rev. Ronald Weryha officiating.  Interment to follow at Round Hill Cemetery, Elizabeth Township. Memorial contributions may be made to the Jefferson Hills Library, 925 Old Clairton Road, Jefferson Hills, PA 15025 or the Lupus Foundation of America, Western PA Chapter, 100 W. Station Square Drive, Suite 1920, Pittsburgh, PA  15219.    



Gifts for your loved one!


 








